Nick Garjiya Mandir Ramnagar, Uttarakhand

·
column9:
Garjiya Mandir Ramnagar Uttarakhand is an ancient temple and one of the Shaktipeeth in India, located in the middle of the Kosi River and dedicated to the goddess Girjia (which literally means the daughter of the mountain, the name of Parvati, the wife of Lord Shiva).

·
column16:
It is situated in Garjiya village of Ramnagar at Nainital district of Uttarakhand.

·
column23:
It is very famous temple of Uttarakhand and one of the oldest Devi temples in India.

·
column30:
The mandir is near Corbett National Park on the way to the Dhikhala zone and museum.

·
column37:
Inside the temple, “Maa Garjiya sits in the center of the temple, adorned with red gold chunri, floral ornaments and garlands, and bless all the bhakts who come to meet her“.

·
column44:
The temple always remain open for its devotee throughout the year.

·
column51:
To get to the top of the temple, you have to climb a steep staircase and there you can see the 4.5 feet tall Garjiya Devi idol. There is an idol of Garjiya Devi, 4.5 feet high, as well as idols of Devi Saraswati, Lord Ganesha and Batuka Bhairava.

·
column58: In Garjiya Mandir, there is also the statue of Laxminarayan which is many years old.

defensecoalore Chet Holmgren of Gonzaga, who is projected to be a top-three pick in the NBA Draft, has declared for the draft.

In only one season, Gonzaga big man Chet Holmgren went from being a highly regarded high school standout to being one of the most promising prospects in college basketball. In the meanwhile, he is preparing to take his abilities to the next level.

In an interview with ESPN's Adrian Wojnarowski on Monday, the first-team All-WCC performer declared his plan to play tic tac toe enter the 2022 NBA draft. It is largely predicted that Holmgren, 19, will be selected in the first three rounds of the draft on June 23.

In the words of Holmgren, after a season in which we did a lot of amazing things as a team and as individuals, I feel like I'm in a position to be able to pursue my longtime ambition of playing in the NBA. Holmgren will now join fellow star Drew Timme in the NBA's prospect pool.

With a five-star recruiting class that included national high school player of the year honors only one year before, Holmgren built up an impressive list of honors in his lone season with the Bulldogs. A standout defensive player in the Western Conference, he was selected Defensive Player of the Year and Newcomer of the Year, as well as being named to the conference's All-Freshman team. Besides that, he was a two-time All-American who finished as a finalist for the Naismith Defensive Player of the Year award as well as a semifinalist for National College Player of the Year award.
